INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2,1,'2014-10-08 20:27:53','2014-10-08 20:27:53','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I work in IT and have too many hobbies.\r\nThis site is an attempt to document my project of refurbishing an 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream travel trailer.</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://github.com/peterolivo\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/v1413577600/Programming-Github-icon_befepn.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" /></a><a href=\"http://twitter.com/peterolivo\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-37\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/v1413577846/twitter-5-xl_coomaa.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" /></a>','About Page','','publish','open','open','','sample-page','','','2014-10-17 20:34:38','2014-10-17 20:34:38','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2014-10-08 20:38:17','2014-10-08 20:38:17','','aistream','','inherit','open','open','','aistream','','','2014-10-08 20:38:17','2014-10-08 20:38:17','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/aistream.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(5,1,'2014-10-13 17:18:36','2014-10-13 17:18:36','','aistream','','inherit','open','open','','aistream-2','','','2014-10-13 17:18:36','2014-10-13 17:18:36','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/aistream.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(6,1,'2014-10-13 17:18:49','2014-10-13 17:18:49','','aistream','','inherit','open','open','','aistream-3','','','2014-10-13 17:18:49','2014-10-13 17:18:49','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/aistream1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(7,1,'2014-10-13 18:04:39','2014-10-13 18:04:39','','aistream','','inherit','open','open','','aistream-4','','','2014-10-13 18:04:39','2014-10-13 18:04:39','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/aistream.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(8,1,'2014-10-13 18:45:20','2014-10-13 18:45:20','','aistream','','inherit','open','open','','aistream-5','','','2014-10-13 18:45:20','2014-10-13 18:45:20','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/aistream.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(9,1,'2014-10-13 18:45:29','2014-10-13 18:45:29','','aistream','','inherit','open','open','','aistream-6','','','2014-10-13 18:45:29','2014-10-13 18:45:29','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/aistream.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(11,1,'2014-10-13 19:29:53','2014-10-13 19:29:53','The journey has begun.\r\n\r\nI recently purchased a 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream trailer. My dreams of creating a tiny live and work space are finally coming to a start. I have often dreamed of a tiny house, living simply and creating a space that can be moved as I journey through life. Working in the tech industry has provided me a grounded basis in ephemeral nature of worldly objects, i.e. I have very little of them. Things I keep are often highly deliberated or passed along for others to enjoy. I plan to create a space where I can harbor these selections and not feel cluttered or intruded upon as large spaces can do. I am excited to clear and re-purpose this trailer into just that. This blog will be stream of consciousness, with the progress of the trailer and related information that is relevant to the progress such as drawings, updates, etc.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of etc. here is a sweet Airstream patch.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-14 aligncenter\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_250/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"246\" />\r\n\r\nEdit: Here is a sweet picture of the trailer courtesy of a friend.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/0IwBtLLl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" /></p>','Airstream Journey','','publish','open','open','','airstream-journey','','','2014-10-28 20:56:46','2014-10-28 20:56:46','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/?p=11',0,'post','',0),(12,1,'2014-10-13 19:28:05','2014-10-13 19:28:05','','airstreamlogo_v9mrup','','inherit','open','open','','airstreamlogo_v9mrup','','','2014-10-13 19:28:05','2014-10-13 19:28:05','',11,'http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_350/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(13,1,'2014-10-13 19:28:16','2014-10-13 19:28:16','The journey has begun.\r\n\r\nI recently purchased a 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream trailer. My dreams of creating a tiny live and work space are finally coming to a start. I have often dreamed of a tiny house, living simply and creating a space that can be moved as I journey through life. Working in the tech industry has provided me a grounded basis in ephemeral nature of worldly objects, i.e. I have very little of them. Things I keep are often highly deliberated or passed along for others to enjoy. I plan to create a space where I can harbor these selections and not feel cluttered or intruded upon as large spaces can do. I am excited to clear and re-purpose this trailer into just that. This blog will be stream of consciousness, with the progress of the trailer and related information that is relevant to the progress such as drawings, updates, etc.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of etc. here is a sweet Airstream patch.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-12\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_350/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"350\" height=\"344\" />','Airstream Journey','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2014-10-13 19:28:16','2014-10-13 19:28:16','',11,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/?p=13',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2014-10-13 19:29:45','2014-10-13 19:29:45','','airstreamlogo_v9mrup','','inherit','open','open','','airstreamlogo_v9mrup-2','','','2014-10-13 19:29:45','2014-10-13 19:29:45','',11,'http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_250/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(15,1,'2014-10-13 19:29:53','2014-10-13 19:29:53','The journey has begun.\r\n\r\nI recently purchased a 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream trailer. My dreams of creating a tiny live and work space are finally coming to a start. I have often dreamed of a tiny house, living simply and creating a space that can be moved as I journey through life. Working in the tech industry has provided me a grounded basis in ephemeral nature of worldly objects, i.e. I have very little of them. Things I keep are often highly deliberated or passed along for others to enjoy. I plan to create a space where I can harbor these selections and not feel cluttered or intruded upon as large spaces can do. I am excited to clear and re-purpose this trailer into just that. This blog will be stream of consciousness, with the progress of the trailer and related information that is relevant to the progress such as drawings, updates, etc.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of etc. here is a sweet Airstream patch.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-14\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_250/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"246\" />','Airstream Journey','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2014-10-13 19:29:53','2014-10-13 19:29:53','',11,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/?p=15',0,'revision','',0),(16,1,'2014-10-13 19:32:02','2014-10-13 19:32:02','','aistream','','inherit','open','open','','aistream-7','','','2014-10-13 19:32:02','2014-10-13 19:32:02','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/aistream.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(17,1,'2014-10-14 01:29:43','2014-10-14 01:29:43','','header','','inherit','open','open','','header','','','2014-10-14 01:29:43','2014-10-14 01:29:43','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/header.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(18,1,'2014-10-14 01:29:56','2014-10-14 01:29:56','http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/cropped-header.png','cropped-header.png','','inherit','open','open','','cropped-header-png','','','2014-10-14 01:29:56','2014-10-14 01:29:56','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/cropped-header.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(19,1,'2014-10-14 02:19:41','2014-10-14 02:19:41','http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/cropped-header_smopk4.png','cropped-header_smopk4.png','','inherit','closed','open','','cropped-header_smopk4-png','','','2014-10-14 02:19:41','2014-10-14 02:19:41','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/header_smopk4.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(20,1,'2014-10-14 02:20:38','2014-10-14 02:20:38','http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/header_smopk4.png','header_smopk4.png','','inherit','open','open','','header_smopk4-png','','','2014-10-14 02:20:38','2014-10-14 02:20:38','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/header_smopk4.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(21,1,'2014-10-14 02:20:52','2014-10-14 02:20:52','http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/header_smopk41.png','header_smopk41.png','','inherit','open','open','','header_smopk41-png','','','2014-10-14 02:20:52','2014-10-14 02:20:52','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/header_smopk41.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(22,1,'2014-10-14 03:00:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Home','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-10-14 03:00:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/?p=22',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(23,1,'2014-10-14 03:00:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-10-14 03:00:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://airstream.uc01.clc.af.cm/?p=23',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(24,1,'2014-10-15 19:21:35','2014-10-15 19:21:35','','aistream','','inherit','open','open','','aistream-8','','','2014-10-15 19:21:35','2014-10-15 19:21:35','',0,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/aistream.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(26,1,'2014-10-17 16:27:28','2014-10-17 16:27:28','The journey has begun.\r\n\r\nI recently purchased a 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream trailer. My dreams of creating a tiny live and work space are finally coming to a start. I have often dreamed of a tiny house, living simply and creating a space that can be moved as I journey through life. Working in the tech industry has provided me a grounded basis in ephemeral nature of worldly objects, i.e. I have very little of them. Things I keep are often highly deliberated or passed along for others to enjoy. I plan to create a space where I can harbor these selections and not feel cluttered or intruded upon as large spaces can do. I am excited to clear and re-purpose this trailer into just that. This blog will be stream of consciousness, with the progress of the trailer and related information that is relevant to the progress such as drawings, updates, etc.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of etc. here is a sweet Airstream patch.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-14 aligncenter\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_250/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"246\" />','Airstream Journey','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 16:27:28','2014-10-17 16:27:28','',11,'http://localhost/?p=26',0,'revision','',0),(27,1,'2014-10-17 17:19:11','2014-10-17 17:19:11','Before I get started on the trailer itself, it needs a nice bed to rest on.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">First, to choose a location. Considering the best use of the yard, as well as the place easiest to maneuver the Airstream into, the south side seemed best. This would allow the awning to be used in its full glory (pics eventually) across the yard, and the trailer would separate the two properties, functioning like a privacy fence. <img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DCjr08Il.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\nInitially the idea was to pour a concrete pad for the Airstream to rest on. But during the clearing and tilling of the yard we found a significant number of old bricks in decent condition that would work just as well. Not to mention they would give the spot a bit of charm, who doesn\'t like re-purposed bricks? Behold the aftermath of junk stone and brick.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/pzG7Ugll.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So, a spot was measured, 6ft by 8ft plot for the bricks to be laid. Tilled it, smoothed it, stomped it and started putting the clay down. Turns out there was roughly a third of the bricks required for the job, but bricks are not hard to come by from many of the crumbling buildings in south St. Louis. Below are a couple pictures of the unfinished pad, which will be completed, leveled and sanded in a future post. The trailer is getting closer to being in position and almost ready for the pulling and striping of the innards. <img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fzr4TMql.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/d0JO7JPl.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Breaking ground.','','publish','open','open','','breaking-ground','','','2014-10-29 14:01:24','2014-10-29 14:01:24','',0,'http://localhost/?p=27',0,'post','',0),(28,1,'2014-10-17 17:19:11','2014-10-17 17:19:11','Before I get started on the trailer itself, it needs a nice bed to rest on.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">First, to choose a location. Considering the best use of the yard as well as the easiest to maneuver into, the south side seemed best. This would allow the awning to be used in its full glory (pics eventually) across the yard, and the trailer would separate the two properties, functioning like a privacy fence. <img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DCjr08I.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"404\" height=\"307\" /></p>\r\nInitially the idea was to pour a concrete pad for the Airstream to rest on. But during the clearing and tilling of the yard we found a significant number of old bricks in decent condition that would work just as well. Not to mention they would give the spot a bit of charm, who doesn\'t like re-purposed bricks? Behold the aftermath of junk stone and brick.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/pzG7Ugl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">So, a spot was measured, 6ft by 8ft plot for the bricks to be laid. Tilled it, smoothed it, stomped it and started putting the clay down. Turns out there was roughly a third of the bricks required for the job, but bricks are not hard to come by from many of the crumbling buildings in south St. Louis. Below are a couple pictures of the unfinished pad, which will be completed, leveled and sanded in a future post. The trailer is getting closer to being in position and almost ready for the pulling and striping of the innards. <img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fzr4TMq.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/d0JO7JP.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>','Breaking ground.','','inherit','open','open','','27-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 17:19:11','2014-10-17 17:19:11','',27,'http://localhost/?p=28',0,'revision','',0),(29,1,'2014-10-17 17:21:56','2014-10-17 17:21:56','The journey has begun.\n\nI recently purchased a 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream trailer. My dreams of creating a tiny live and work space are finally coming to a start. I have often dreamed of a tiny house, living simply and creating a space that can be moved as I journey through life. Working in the tech industry has provided me a grounded basis in ephemeral nature of worldly objects, i.e. I have very little of them. Things I keep are often highly deliberated or passed along for others to enjoy. I plan to create a space where I can harbor these selections and not feel cluttered or intruded upon as large spaces can do. I am excited to clear and re-purpose this trailer into just that. This blog will be stream of consciousness, with the progress of the trailer and related information that is relevant to the progress such as drawings, updates, etc.\n\nSpeaking of etc. here is a sweet Airstream patch.\n\n<img class=\"wp-image-14 aligncenter\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_250/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"246\" />\n\nEdit: Here is a sweet picture of the trailer courtesy of a friend.','Airstream Journey','','inherit','open','open','','11-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-17 17:21:56','2014-10-17 17:21:56','',11,'http://localhost/?p=29',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2014-10-17 17:22:18','2014-10-17 17:22:18','The journey has begun.\r\n\r\nI recently purchased a 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream trailer. My dreams of creating a tiny live and work space are finally coming to a start. I have often dreamed of a tiny house, living simply and creating a space that can be moved as I journey through life. Working in the tech industry has provided me a grounded basis in ephemeral nature of worldly objects, i.e. I have very little of them. Things I keep are often highly deliberated or passed along for others to enjoy. I plan to create a space where I can harbor these selections and not feel cluttered or intruded upon as large spaces can do. I am excited to clear and re-purpose this trailer into just that. This blog will be stream of consciousness, with the progress of the trailer and related information that is relevant to the progress such as drawings, updates, etc.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of etc. here is a sweet Airstream patch.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-14 aligncenter\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_250/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"246\" />\r\n\r\nEdit: Here is a sweet picture of the trailer courtesy of a friend.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/0IwBtLL.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" /></p>','Airstream Journey','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 17:22:18','2014-10-17 17:22:18','',11,'http://localhost/?p=30',0,'revision','',0),(31,1,'2014-10-17 17:40:51','2014-10-17 17:40:51','Before I get started on the trailer itself, it needs a nice bed to rest on.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">First, to choose a location. Considering the best use of the yard as well as the easiest to maneuver into, the south side seemed best. This would allow the awning to be used in its full glory (pics eventually) across the yard, and the trailer would separate the two properties, functioning like a privacy fence. <img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DCjr08I.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"404\" height=\"307\" /></p>\r\nInitially the idea was to pour a concrete pad for the Airstream to rest on. But during the clearing and tilling of the yard we found a significant number of old bricks in decent condition that would work just as well. Not to mention they would give the spot a bit of charm, who doesn\'t like re-purposed bricks? Behold the aftermath of junk stone and brick.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/pzG7Ugl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So, a spot was measured, 6ft by 8ft plot for the bricks to be laid. Tilled it, smoothed it, stomped it and started putting the clay down. Turns out there was roughly a third of the bricks required for the job, but bricks are not hard to come by from many of the crumbling buildings in south St. Louis. Below are a couple pictures of the unfinished pad, which will be completed, leveled and sanded in a future post. The trailer is getting closer to being in position and almost ready for the pulling and striping of the innards. <img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fzr4TMq.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/d0JO7JP.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>','Breaking ground.','','inherit','open','open','','27-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 17:40:51','2014-10-17 17:40:51','',27,'http://localhost/?p=31',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2014-10-17 20:33:33','2014-10-17 20:33:33','This site is an attempt to document my project of refurbishing an 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream travel trailer.\nI work in IT and have too many hobbies.\n\n<a href=\"http://github.com/peterolivo\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/v1413577600/Programming-Github-icon_befepn.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" /></a><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-37\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/v1413577846/twitter-5-xl_coomaa.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" />','About Page','','inherit','open','open','','2-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-17 20:33:33','2014-10-17 20:33:33','',2,'http://localhost/?p=32',0,'revision','',0),(33,1,'2014-10-17 17:46:22','2014-10-17 17:46:22','This is the about page. I will update this later with things that should be here.','About Page','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 17:46:22','2014-10-17 17:46:22','',2,'http://localhost/?p=33',0,'revision','',0),(34,1,'2014-10-17 20:01:42','2014-10-17 20:01:42','Before I get started on the trailer itself, it needs a nice bed to rest on.\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">First, to choose a location. Considering the best use of the yard, as well as the place easiest to maneuver the Airstream into, the south side seemed best. This would allow the awning to be used in its full glory (pics eventually) across the yard, and the trailer would separate the two properties, functioning like a privacy fence. <img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DCjr08I.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"404\" height=\"307\" /></p>\nInitially the idea was to pour a concrete pad for the Airstream to rest on. But during the clearing and tilling of the yard we found a significant number of old bricks in decent condition that would work just as well. Not to mention they would give the spot a bit of charm, who doesn\'t like re-purposed bricks? Behold the aftermath of junk stone and brick.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/pzG7Ugl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So, a spot was measured, 6ft by 8ft plot for the bricks to be laid. Tilled it, smoothed it, stomped it and started putting the clay down. Turns out there was roughly a third of the bricks required for the job, but bricks are not hard to come by from many of the crumbling buildings in south St. Louis. Below are a couple pictures of the unfinished pad, which will be completed, leveled and sanded in a future post. The trailer is getting closer to being in position and almost ready for the pulling and striping of the innards. <img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fzr4TMq.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/d0JO7JP.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>','Breaking ground.','','inherit','open','open','','27-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-17 20:01:42','2014-10-17 20:01:42','',27,'http://localhost/?p=34',0,'revision','',0),(35,1,'2014-10-17 20:01:43','2014-10-17 20:01:43','Before I get started on the trailer itself, it needs a nice bed to rest on.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">First, to choose a location. Considering the best use of the yard, as well as the place easiest to maneuver the Airstream into, the south side seemed best. This would allow the awning to be used in its full glory (pics eventually) across the yard, and the trailer would separate the two properties, functioning like a privacy fence. <img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DCjr08I.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"404\" height=\"307\" /></p>\r\nInitially the idea was to pour a concrete pad for the Airstream to rest on. But during the clearing and tilling of the yard we found a significant number of old bricks in decent condition that would work just as well. Not to mention they would give the spot a bit of charm, who doesn\'t like re-purposed bricks? Behold the aftermath of junk stone and brick.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/pzG7Ugl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So, a spot was measured, 6ft by 8ft plot for the bricks to be laid. Tilled it, smoothed it, stomped it and started putting the clay down. Turns out there was roughly a third of the bricks required for the job, but bricks are not hard to come by from many of the crumbling buildings in south St. Louis. Below are a couple pictures of the unfinished pad, which will be completed, leveled and sanded in a future post. The trailer is getting closer to being in position and almost ready for the pulling and striping of the innards. <img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fzr4TMq.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/d0JO7JP.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>','Breaking ground.','','inherit','open','open','','27-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 20:01:43','2014-10-17 20:01:43','',27,'http://localhost/?p=35',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2014-10-17 20:19:37','2014-10-17 20:19:37','This site is an attempt to document my project of refurbishing an 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream travel trailer.\r\nI work in IT and have too many hobbies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n','About Page','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 20:19:37','2014-10-17 20:19:37','',2,'http://localhost/?p=36',0,'revision','',0),(37,1,'2014-10-17 20:22:46','2014-10-17 20:22:46','',