nter wp-image-37\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/v1413577846/twitter-5-xl_coomaa.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" /></a>','About Page','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 20:34:04','2014-10-17 20:34:04','',2,'http://localhost/?p=43',0,'revision','',0),(44,1,'2014-10-17 20:34:38','2014-10-17 20:34:38','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I work in IT and have too many hobbies.\r\nThis site is an attempt to document my project of refurbishing an 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream travel trailer.</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://github.com/peterolivo\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/v1413577600/Programming-Github-icon_befepn.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" /></a><a href=\"http://twitter.com/peterolivo\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-37\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/v1413577846/twitter-5-xl_coomaa.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" /></a>','About Page','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 20:34:38','2014-10-17 20:34:38','',2,'http://localhost/?p=44',0,'revision','',0),(45,1,'2014-10-20 18:46:54','2014-10-20 18:46:54','We got a lot of bricks laid.\r\n\r\nOk so, after a meager attempt at creating a brick pad for the Airstream, it was started over. After finding a lot of cheap bricks around the corner from the house, we put down some sand and got a brickin\'.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/6fpF1jll.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/0yAwU4kl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAfter some leveling problems, we got the pad straight and level. Not the best, but enough for its purpose. The pad may be surrounded by some of the rock laying around if it seems appropriate after the trailer is in place.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/gu9ni4ol.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAs it turned out, we had way too many bricks. So we got creative and made a little walkway out of the extra. Its not enough, but there are more bricks that can be uncovered from the yard (If I ever want to drag them out, ugh).\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/sIZfz1vl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nIt all turned out very nice, after a good rain the bricks should settle a good amount.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ajSqC6kl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Bricks, all day.','','publish','open','open','','bricks-all-day','','','2014-10-28 21:00:56','2014-10-28 21:00:56','',0,'http://localhost/?p=45',0,'post','',0),(46,1,'2014-10-20 18:45:59','2014-10-20 18:45:59','We got a lot of bricks laid.\r\n\r\nOk so, after a meger attempt at creating a brick pad for the Airstream, it was started over. After finding a lot of cheap bricks around the corner from the house, we put down some sand and got a brickin\'.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/6fpF1jl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/0yAwU4k.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nAfter some leveling problems, we got the pad straight and level. Not the best, but enough for its purpose. The pad may be surrounded by some of the rock laying around if it seems appropriate after the trailer is in place.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/gu9ni4o.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nAs it turned out, we had way too many bricks. So we got creative and made a little walkway out of the extra. Its not enough, but there are more bricks that can be uncovered from the yard (If I ever want to drag them out, ugh).\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/sIZfz1v.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nIt all turned out very nice, after a good rain they should settle a good amount.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ajSqC6k.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Bricks, all day.','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-v1','','','2014-10-20 18:45:59','2014-10-20 18:45:59','',45,'http://localhost/?p=46',0,'revision','',0),(47,1,'2014-10-20 18:46:54','2014-10-20 18:46:54','We got a lot of bricks laid.\r\n\r\nOk so, after a