out of the extra. Its not enough, but there are more bricks that can be uncovered from the yard (If I ever want to drag them out, ugh).\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/sIZfz1v.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nIt all turned out very nice, after a good rain the bricks should settle a good amount.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ajSqC6k.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Bricks, all day.','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-v1','','','2014-10-20 18:48:14','2014-10-20 18:48:14','',45,'http://localhost/?p=48',0,'revision','',0),(49,1,'2014-10-23 19:25:00','2014-10-23 19:25:00','Bags, and friends.\r\n\r\nQuick update for today. Just sanded the top of the pad. Now we are ready for the trailer to be moved into position. \r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://i.imgur.com/18vYWIhl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAnd a quick promotional shoutout to Bob, my roommate, who has been helping on this project. Check out his own blog, about cool projects and the daily grind.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.makeandmake.com/\" title=\"http://www.makeandmake.com/\">http://www.makeandmake.com/</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Sandy Bags.','','publish','open','open','','sandy-bags','','','2014-10-28 21:02:44','2014-10-28 21:02:44','',0,'http://localhost/?p=49',0,'post','',0),(50,1,'2014-10-23 19:24:26','2014-10-23 19:24:26','Bags, and friends.\r\n\r\nQuick update for today. Just sanded the top of the pad. Now we are ready for the trailer to be moved into position. \r\n<img src=\"http://i.imgur.com/18vYWIh.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAnd a quick promotional shoutout to Bob, my roommate who has been helping on this project. Check out his own blog, about cool projects and the daily grind.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.makeandmake.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n','Sandy Bags.','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-v1','','','2014-10-23 19:24:26','2014-10-23 19:24:26','',49,'http://localhost/?p=50',0,'revision','',0),(51,1,'2014-10-23 19:25:00','2014-10-23 19:25:00','Bags, and friends.\r\n\r\nQuick update for today. Just sanded the top of the pad. Now we are ready for the trailer to be moved into position. \r\n<img src=\"http://i.imgur.com/18vYWIh.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAnd a quick promotional shoutout to Bob, my roommate, who has been helping on this project. Check out his own blog, about cool projects and the daily grind.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.makeandmake.com/\" title=\"http://www.makeandmake.com/\">http://www.makeandmake.com/</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Sandy Bags.','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-v1','','','2014-10-23 19:25:00','2014-10-23 19:25:00','',49,'http://localhost/?p=51',0,'revision','',0),(52,1,'2014-10-28 19:47:40','2014-10-28 19:47:40','Last weekend, the long awaited positioning of the trailer happened.\r\n\r\nAs soon as it begun, the undertaking of moving the trailer into place seemed overwhelming. We had a truck big enough, a Chevy Diesel, but needed to cut the fence down to get the trailer into place.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DtAUbBHl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/actDMl4l.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/KjhQF6Ol.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nTurns out, the truck was too big. The dual axle truck could not fit through the fence, the fence that we cut out.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/4aScu2tl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ePHQLCcl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nThen in response to using a big truck, the small 22re Toyota truck was used. It was too underpowered and moved the Airstream a few feet before smoking the clutch.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/NM4oRpIl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nWe were able to get the trailer in with a Ford F150, and a Ford Explorer. It involved large ammounts of coordination within the yard, and switching hitch positions, so I have no pictures that process.\r\n\r\nIn the end, the brick pad was a mess, but the trailer was in place. So we burned some trash from the yard. It was <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8CPlF-IEkXQ\">a good day</a>.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/u50GpvDl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n','Metal Tube Going In.','','publish','open','open','','metal-tube-going-in','','','2014-10-28 21:01:57','2014-10-28 21:01:57','',0,'http://localhost/?p=52',0,'post','',0),(53,1,'2014-10-28 19:47:40','2014-10-28 19:47:40','This weekend, the long awaited position of the trailer happened.\r\n\r\nAs soon as it begun, the undertaking of moving the trailer into place seemed overwhelming. We had a truck big enough, a Chevy Diesel, but needed to cut the fence down to get the trailer into place.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DtAUbBH.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/actDMl4.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/KjhQF6O.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nTurns out, the truck was too big. The dual axle truck could noy fit through the fence, the fence that we cut out.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/4aScu2t.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ePHQLCc.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nThen in response to using a big truck, the small 22re Toyota truck was used. It was too underpowered and moved the Airstream a few feet before smoking the clutch.\r\n\r\nWe were able to get the trailer in with a Ford F150, and a Ford Explorer. It involved large ammounts of coordination within the yard, and switching hitch positions, so I have no pictures that process.\r\n\r\nIn the end, the brick pad was a mess, but the trailer was in place. So we burned some trash from the yard. It was <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8CPlF-IEkXQ\">a good day</a>.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/u50GpvD.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n','Metal Tube Going In.','','inherit','open','open','','52-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 19:47:40','2014-10-28 19:47:40','',52,'http://localhost/?p=53',0,'revision','',0),(54,1,'2014-10-28 19:49:14','2014-10-28 19:49:14','Last weekend, the long awaited positioning of the trailer happened.\r\n\r