h the fence, the fence that we cut out.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/4aScu2t.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ePHQLCc.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nThen in response to using a big truck, the small 22re Toyota truck was used. It was too underpowered and moved the Airstream a few feet before smoking the clutch.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/NM4oRpI.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nWe were able to get the trailer in with a Ford F150, and a Ford Explorer. It involved large ammounts of coordination within the yard, and switching hitch positions, so I have no pictures that process.\r\n\r\nIn the end, the brick pad was a mess, but the trailer was in place. So we burned some trash from the yard. It was <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8CPlF-IEkXQ\">a good day</a>.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/u50GpvD.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n','Metal Tube Going In.','','inherit','open','open','','52-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 19:53:00','2014-10-28 19:53:00','',52,'http://localhost/?p=56',0,'revision','',0),(57,1,'2014-10-28 19:56:57','2014-10-28 19:56:57','The Airstream in position and the awning in its full glory for the first time.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cxuJbKGl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Awningsome','','publish','open','open','','awningsome','','','2014-10-28 21:02:11','2014-10-28 21:02:11','',0,'http://localhost/?p=57',0,'post','',0),(58,1,'2014-10-28 19:56:57','2014-10-28 19:56:57','The awning in its full glory and Airstream in position for the first time.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cxuJbKG.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Awningsome','','inherit','open','open','','57-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 19:56:57','2014-10-28 19:56:57','',57,'http://localhost/?p=58',0,'revision','',0),(59,1,'2014-10-28 19:57:50','2014-10-28 19:57:50','The Airstream in position and the awning in its full glory for the first time.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cxuJbKG.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Awningsome','','inherit','open','open','','57-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 19:57:50','2014-10-28 19:57:50','',57,'http://localhost/?p=59',0,'revision','',0),(60,1,'2014-10-28 20:56:46','2014-10-28 20:56:46','The journey has begun.\r\n\r\nI recently purchased a 1978 Excella 500 31\' Airstream trailer. My dreams of creating a tiny live and work space are finally coming to a start. I have often dreamed of a tiny house, living simply and creating a space that can be moved as I journey through life. Working in the tech industry has provided me a grounded basis in ephemeral nature of worldly objects, i.e. I have very little of them. Things I keep are often highly deliberated or passed along for others to enjoy. I plan to create a space where I can harbor these selections and not feel cluttered or intruded upon as large spaces can do. I am excited to clear and re-purpose this trailer into just that. This blog will be stream of consciousness, with the progress of the trailer and related information that is relevant to the progress such as drawings, updates, etc.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of etc. here is a sweet Airstream patch.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-14 aligncenter\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/hpuomxzff/image/upload/c_scale,w_250/v1413228456/airstreamlogo_v9mrup.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"246\" />\r\n\r\nEdit: Here is a sweet picture of the trailer courtesy of a friend.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/0IwBtLLl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" /></p>','Airstream Journey','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 20:56:46','2014-10-28 20:56:46','',11,'http://localhost/?p=60',0,'revision','',0),(61,1,'2014-10-28 20:57:15','2014-10-28 20:57:15','Before I get started on the trailer itself, it needs a nice bed to rest on.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">First, to choose a location. Considering the best use of the yard, as well as the place easiest to maneuver the Airstream into, the south side seemed best. This would allow the awning to be used in its full glory (pics eventually) across the yard, and the trailer would separate the two properties, functioning like a privacy fence. <img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DCjr08Il.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"404\" height=\"307\" /></p>\r\nInitially the idea was to pour a concrete pad for the Airstream to rest on. But during the clearing and tilling of the yard we found a significant number of old bricks in decent condition that would work just as well. Not to mention they would give the spot a bit of charm, who doesn\'t like re-purposed bricks? Behold the aftermath of junk stone and brick.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/pzG7Ugll.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So, a spot was measured, 6ft by 8ft plot for the bricks to be laid. Tilled it, smoothed it, stomped it and started putting the clay down. Turns out there was roughly a third of the bricks required for the job, but bricks are not hard to come by from many of the crumbling buildings in south St. Louis. Below are a couple pictures of the unfinished pad, which will be completed, leveled and sanded in a future post. The trailer is getting closer to being in position and almost ready for the pulling and striping of the innards. <img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fzr4TMq.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/d0JO7JPl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"4208\" height=\"3120\" /></p>','Breaking ground.','','inherit','open','open','','27-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 20:57:15','2014-10-28 20:57:15','',27,'http://localhost/?p=61',0,'revision','',0),(62,1,'2014-10-28 20:58:00','2014-10-28 20:58:00','We got a lot of bricks laid.\r\n\r\nOk so, after a meager attempt at creating a brick pad for the Airstream, it was started over. After finding a lot of cheap bricks around the corner from the house, we put down some sand and got a brickin\'.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/6fpF1jll.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/0yAwU4kl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAfter some leveling problems, we got the pad straight and level. Not the best, but enough for its purpose. The pad may be surrounded by some of the rock laying around if it seems appropriate after the trailer is in place.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/gu9ni4ol.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAs it turned out, we had way too many bricks. So we got creative and made a little walkway out of the extra. Its not enough, but there are more bricks that can be uncovered from the yard (If I ever want to drag them out, ugh).\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/sIZfz1vl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nIt all turned out very nice, after a good rain the bricks should settle a good amount.\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ajSqC6kl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Bricks, all day.','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 20:58:00','2014-10-28 20:58:00','',45,'http://localhost/?p=62',0,'revision','',0),(63,1,'2014-10-28 20:58:58','2014-10-28 20:58:58','We got a lot of bricks laid.\r\n\r\nOk so, after a meager attempt at creating a brick pad for the Airstream, it was started over. After finding a lot of cheap bricks around the corner from the house, we put down some sand and got a brickin\'.\r\n<center>\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/6fpF1jll.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/0yAwU4kl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n</center>\r\nAfter some leveling problems, we got the pad straight and level. Not the best, but enough for its purpose. The pad may be surrounded by some of the rock laying around if it seems appropriate after the trailer is in place.\r\n<center>\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/gu9ni4ol.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n</center>\r\nAs it turned out, we had way too many bricks. So we got creative and made a little walkway out of the extra. Its not enough, but there are more bricks that can be uncovered from the yard (If I ever want to drag them out, ugh).\r\n<center>\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/sIZfz1vl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n</center>\r\nIt all turned out very nice, after a good rain the bricks should settle a good amount.\r\n<center>\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ajSqC6kl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n</center>','Bricks, all day.','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 20:58:58','2014-10-28 20:58:58','',45,'http://localhost/?p=63',0,'revision','',0),(64,1,'2014-10-28 21:00:56','2014-10-28 21:00:56','We got a lot of bricks laid.\r\n\r\nOk so, after a meager attempt at creating a brick pad for the Airstream, it was started over. After finding a lot of cheap bricks around the corner from the house, we put down some sand and got a brickin\'.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/6fpF1jll.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/0yAwU4kl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAfter some leveling problems, we got the pad straight and level. Not the best, but enough for its purpose. The pad may be surrounded by some of the rock laying around if it seems appropriate after the trailer is in place.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/gu9ni4ol.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAs it turned out, we had way too many bricks. So we got creative and made a little walkway out of the extra. Its not enough, but there are more bricks that can be uncovered from the yard (If I ever want to drag them out, ugh).\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/sIZfz1vl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nIt all turned out very nice, after a good rain the bricks should settle a good amount.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ajSqC6kl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Bricks, all day.','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 21:00:56','2014-10-28 21:00:56','',45,'http://localhost/?p=64',0,'revision','',0),(65,1,'2014-10-28 21:01:19','2014-10-28 21:01:19','Bags, and friends.\r\n\r\nQuick update for today. Just sanded the top of the pad. Now we are ready for the trailer to be moved into position. \r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://i.imgur.com/18vYWIh.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nAnd a quick promotional shoutout to Bob, my roommate, who has been helping on this project. Check out his own blog, about cool projects and the daily grind.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.makeandmake.com/\" title=\"http://www.makeandmake.com/\">http://www.makeandmake.com/</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Sandy Bags.','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 21:01:19','2014-10-28 21:01:19','',49,'http://localhost/?p=65',0,'revision','',0),(66,1,'2014-10-28 21:01:57','2014-10-28 21:01:57','Last weekend, the long awaited positioning of the trailer happened.\r\n\r\nAs soon as it begun, the undertaking of moving the trailer into place seemed overwhelming. We had a truck big enough, a Chevy Diesel, but needed to cut the fence down to get the trailer into place.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/DtAUbBHl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/actDMl4l.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/KjhQF6Ol.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nTurns out, the truck was too big. The dual axle truck could not fit through the fence, the fence that we cut out.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/4aScu2tl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ePHQLCcl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nThen in response to using a big truck, the small 22re Toyota truck was used. It was too underpowered and moved the Airstream a few feet before smoking the clutch.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/NM4oRpIl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\nWe were able to get the trailer in with a Ford F150, and a Ford Explorer. It involved large ammounts of coordination within the yard, and switching hitch positions, so I have no pictures that process.\r\n\r\nIn the end, the brick pad was a mess, but the trailer was in place. So we burned some trash from 