railer is outside, which is a bit perturbing because of the trailer plumbing lines, but considering I plan on replacing a lot of the them anyway...\r\n\r\nIt does make for a hell of a picture though.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://i.imgur.com/zmGStATl.jpg\" alt=\"\" />','Winter Wonderland','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-v1','','','2014-11-17 18:09:59','2014-11-17 18:09:59','',86,'http://localhost/?p=88',0,'revision','',0),(89,1,'2014-12-01 18:29:34','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-01 18:29:34','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost/?p=89',0,'post','',0),(90,1,'2014-12-01 18:43:32','2014-12-01 18:43:32','Here is a look at what the studio portion of the trailer will look like.\r\n\r\nThe winter has made it less desirable to continue working on the physical potions of the trailer. So I have gone to the drawing board.\r\nTook a few interior pitures of the trailer to start fleshing out the ideas I have for the studio portion of the Airstream. The front of the trailer, one of the round sections, normally has a couch as the living room section. Though it is sad to see the couch go this will make a great desk section and the round walls will elimiate the need for bass traps. Also the large ammount of windows there will make working at the desk a pleasure.\r\nI am still thinking about a creative way have the desk double as a place to watch TV, or some other use, we shall see.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://i.imgur.com/rkHf4Jnl.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\nUpdate: Also, If you notice, the built in speakers will be nice as an alternate pair of reference monitors.','Studio Concept','','publish','open','open','','studio-concept','','','2014-12-01 22:05:12','2014-12-01 22:05:12','',0,'http://localhost/?p=90',0,'post','',0),(91,1,'2014-12-01 18:43:32','2014-12-01 18:43:32','Here is a look at what the studio portion of the trailer will look like.\r\n\r\nThe winter has made it less desirable t